commentAnnotations.text: Bridging therapy: At the discretion of the investigator, corticosteroid bridging therapy may be considered for subjects with high disease burden at screening.
Disease Assessments: Calculated from the day of randomization and not the date of dosing with axicabtagene ciloleucel or SOC therapy.

After completing at least 60 months of assessments in Study KTE-C19-107, subjects who received at least one dose of axicabtagene ciloleucel as protocol therapy will complete the remainder of the 15-year follow-up assessments in a separate LTFU study.
Minimum observation period: 7 days unless otherwise required by country regulatory agencies (refer to Appendix D).
